<h2 id="introduction-to-artificial-intelligence">Introduction to Artificial Intelligence</h2>

<p><small class="gray">
alongside Willie Wilson
</small> <big>|</big> <small class="gray">Fall
2018
</small></p>

<p>Students learn the foundational aspects of artificial intelligence. Topics include logic, symbolic knowledge representation, search and problem solving, and statistical methods. Heavier on classical AI and logic.</p>

<h2 id="introduction-to-game-design">Introduction to Game Design</h2>

<p><small class="gray">
alongside Ken Forbus
</small> <big>|</big> <small class="gray">Spring
2017
</small></p>

<p>Students learn how games are designed, and create their own. Topics include game mechanic, game engine architecture, and industry practice. Since discontinued at Northwestern, this class was one of the oldest university game design courses in the country.</p>

